{
  "text": "Authority.commit (using APIs) 1 MB Authority.commit (one-time setup for full node) 126 GB Authority.commit (using full node) 235 B Auditor.sync 37.4 MB Auditor.prove_incl 1.3 kB scenario, we consider the maximum number of transactions that can fit into a block. Currently, the Bitcoin block size limit is 1 MB, up to 97 bytes of which is non-transaction data. [CITATION_1] The minimum transaction size is 166 bytes, 5 so the upper bound on the number of transactions in a given block is 6,023. While this is far higher than the number of transactions that Bitcoin blocks currently contain, [CITATION_2] we nevertheless use it as a worst-case cost and an acknowledgment that Bitcoin is evolving and blocks may grow in the future.",
